  "text": "Confirmation of pulmonary tumor emboli require a lung biopsy procedure, which can be done with either open-lung or transbronchial approaches [CITATION_1] . A definitive diagnosis of pulmonary tumor emboli through invasive procedures was not pursued in our patient since surgery was already done, and the patient was started on warfarin. The fact that no recurrence of PE happened during the follow-up may favor but does not confirm that the emboli were thrombotic in origin.",
